<?php 
switch($verse){
case 1:{?>Their reckoning draweth nigh for mankind, while they turn away in heedlessness.<?php break;}
case 2:{?>Never cometh there unto them a new reminder from their Lord but they listen to it while they play.<?php break;}
case 3:{?>With hearts preoccupied. And they confer in secret The wrong doers say : Is this other than a mortal like you? Will ye then succumb to magic when ye see ( it )?<?php break;}
case 4:{?>He saith : My Lord knoweth what is spoken in the heaven and the earth. He is the Hearer, the Knower.<?php break;}
case 5:{?>Nay, say they, ( these are but ) muddled dreams; nay, he hath but invented it; nay, he is but a poet. Let him bring us a portent even as those of old ( who were God ' s messengers ) were sent ( with portents ).<?php break;}
case 6:{?>Not a township believed of those which We destroyed before them ( though We sent them portents ) : would they then believe?<?php break;}
case 7:{?>And We sent not ( as Our messengers ) before thee other than men whom We inspired. Ask the followers of the Reminder if ye know not?<?php break;}
case 8:{?>We gave them not bodies that would not eat food, nor were they immortals.<?php break;}
case 9:{?>Then We fulfilled the promise unto them. So We delivered them and whom We would, and We destroyed the prodigals.<?php break;}
case 10:{?>Now We have revealed unto you a Scripture wherein is your Reminder. Have ye then no sense?<?php break;}
case 11:{?>How many a community that dealt unjustly have We shattered, and raised up after them another folk!<?php break;}
case 12:{?>And, when they felt Our might, behold them fleeing from it!<?php break;}
case 13:{?>( But it was said unto them ) : Flee not, but return to that ( existence ) which emasculated you and to your dwellings, that ye may be questioned.<?php break;}
case 14:{?>They cried : Alas for us! Lo! we were wrongdoers.<?php break;}
case 15:{?>And this their crying ceased not till We made them as reaped corn, extinct.<?php break;}
case 16:{?>We created not the heaven and the earth and all that is between them in play.<?php break;}
case 17:{?>If We had wished to find a pastime, We could have found it in Our presence if We ever did.<?php break;}
case 18:{?>Nay, but We hurl the true against the false, and it doth break its head and lo! it vanisheth. And yours will be woe for that which ye ascribe ( unto Him ).<?php break;}
case 19:{?>Unto Him belongeth whosoever is in the heavens and the earth. And those who dwell in His presence are not too proud to worship Him nor do they weary;<?php break;}
case 20:{?>They glorify ( Him ) night and day; they flag not.<?php break;}
case 21:{?>Or have they chosen Gods from the earth who raise the dead?<?php break;}
case 22:{?>If there were therein Gods beside Allah, then verily both ( the heavens and the earth ) had been disordered. Glorified be Allah, the Lord of the Throne, from all that they ascribe ( unto Him ).<?php break;}
case 23:{?>He will not be questioned as to that which He doeth, but they will be questioned.<?php break;}
case 24:{?>Or have they chosen other gods beside Him? Say : Bring your proof ( of their godhead ). This is the Reminder of those with me and those before me, but most of them know not the Truth and so they are averse.<?php break;}
case 25:{?>And We sent no messenger before thee but We inspired him, ( saying ) : There is no God save Me ( Allah ), so worship Me.<?php break;}
case 26:{?>And they say : The Beneficent hath taken unto Himself a son. Be He glorified! Nay, but ( those whom they call sons ) are honored slaves;<?php break;}
case 27:{?>They speak not until He hath spoken, and they act by His command.<?php break;}
case 28:{?>He knoweth what is before them and what is behind them, and they cannot intercede except for him whom He accepteth, and they quake for awe of Him.<?php break;}
case 29:{?>And one of them who should say : Lo! I am a God beside Him, that one We should repay with hell. Thus We repay wrong doers.<?php break;}
case 30:{?>Have not those who disbelieve known that the heavens and the earth were of one piece, then We parted them, and We made every living thing of water? Will they not then believe?<?php break;}
case 31:{?>And We have placed in the earth firm hills lest it quake with them, and We have placed therein ravines as roads that haply they may find their way.<?php break;}
case 32:{?>And We have made the sky a roof withheld ( from them ). Yet they turn away from its portents.<?php break;}
case 33:{?>And He it is Who created the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. They float, each in an orbit.<?php break;}
case 34:{?>We appointed immortality for no mortal before thee. What! if thou diest, can they be immortal?<?php break;}
case 35:{?>Every soul must taste of death, and We try you with evil and with good, for ordeal. And unto Us ye will be returned.<?php break;}
case 36:{?>And when those who disbelieve behold thee, they but choose thee out for mockery, ( saying ) : Is this he who maketh mention of your gods? And they would deny all mention of the Beneficent.<?php break;}
case 37:{?>Man is made of haste. I shall show you My portents, but ask Me not to hasten.<?php break;}
case 38:{?>And they say : When will this promise ( be fulfilled ), if ye are truthful?<?php break;}
case 39:{?>If those who disbelieved but knew the time when they will not be able to drive off the fire from their faces and from their backs, and they will not be helped!<?php break;}
case 40:{?>Nay, but it will come upon them unawares so that it will stupefy them, and they will be unable to repel it, neither will they be reprieved.<?php break;}
case 41:{?>Messengers before thee, indeed, were mocked, but that whereat they mocked surrounded those who scoffed at them.<?php break;}
case 42:{?>Say : Who guardeth you in the night or in the day from the Beneficent? Nay, but they turn away from mention of their Lord,<?php break;}
case 43:{?>Or have they gods who can shield them from Us? They cannot help themselves nor can they be defended from Us.<?php break;}
case 44:{?>Nay, but We gave these and their fathers ease until life grew long for them. See they not how we visit the land, reducing it of its outlying parts? Can they then be the victors?<?php break;}
case 45:{?>Say ( O Muhammad, unto mankind ) : I warn you only by the Inspiration. But the deaf hear not the call when they are warned.<?php break;}
case 46:{?>And if a breath of thy Lord ' s punishment were to touch them, they assuredly would say : Alas for us! Lo! we were wrong doers.<?php break;}
case 47:{?>And We set a just balance for the Day of Resurrection so that no soul is wronged in aught. Though it be of the weight of a grain of mustard seed, We bring it. And We suffice for reckoners.<?php break;}
case 48:{?>And We verily gave Moses and Aaron the Criterion ( of right and wrong ) and a light and a Reader far those who keep from evil<?php break;}
case 49:{?>Those who tear their Lord in secret and who dread the Hour ( of doom ).<?php break;}
case 50:{?>This is a blessed Reminder that We have revealed : Will ye then reject it?<?php break;}
case 51:{?>And We verily gave Abraham of old his proper course, and We were Aware of him,<?php break;}
case 52:{?>When he said unto his father and his folk : What are these images unto which ye pay devotion?<?php break;}
case 53:{?>They said : We found our fathers worshippers of them.<?php break;}
case 54:{?>He said : Verily ye and your fathers were in plain error.<?php break;}
case 55:{?>They said : Bringest thou unto us the truth, or art thou some jester?<?php break;}
case 56:{?>He said : Nay, but your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, Who created them; and I am of those who testify unto that.<?php break;}
case 57:{?>And, by Allah, I shall circumvent your idols after ye have gone away and turned your backs.<?php break;}
case 58:{?>Then he reduced them to fragments, all save the chief of them, that haply they might have recourse to it.<?php break;}
case 59:{?>They said : Who hath done this to our gods? Surely it must be some evil doer.<?php break;}
case 60:{?>They said : We heard a youth make mention of them, who is called Abraham.<?php break;}
case 61:{?>They said : Then bring him ( hither ) before the people ' s eyes that they may testify.<?php break;}
case 62:{?>They said : Is it thou who hast done this to our gods, O Abraham?<?php break;}
case 63:{?>He said : But this, their chief hath done it. So question them, if they can speak.<?php break;}
case 64:{?>Then gathered they apart and said : Lo! ye yourselves are the wrong doers.<?php break;}
case 65:{?>And they were utterly confounded, and they said : Well thou knowest that these speak not.<?php break;}
case 66:{?>He said : Worship ye then instead of Allah that which cannot profit you at all, nor harm you?<?php break;}
case 67:{?>Fie on you and all that ye worship instead of Allah! Have ye then no sense?<?php break;}
case 68:{?>They cried : Burn him and stand by your gods, if ye will be doing.<?php break;}
case 69:{?>We said : O fire, be coolness and peace for Abraham.<?php break;}
case 70:{?>And they wished to set a snare for him, but We made them the greater losers.<?php break;}
case 71:{?>And We rescued him and Lot ( and brought them ) to the land which We have blessed for ( all ) peoples.<?php break;}
case 72:{?>And We bestowed upon him Isaac, and Jacob as a grandson. Each of them We made righteous.<?php break;}
case 73:{?>And We made them chiefs who guide by Our command, and We inspired in them the doing of good deeds and the right establishment of worship and the giving of alms and they were worshippers of Us ( alone ).<?php break;}
case 74:{?>And unto Lot We gave judgment and knowledge, and We delivered him from the community that did abominations. Lo! they were folk of evil, lewd.<?php break;}
case 75:{?>And We brought him in unto Our mercy. Lo! he was of the righteous.<?php break;}
case 76:{?>And Noah, when he cried of old, We heard his prayer and saved him and his household from the great affliction.<?php break;}
case 77:{?>And delivered him from the people who denied Our revelations. Lo! they were folk of evil, therefor did We drown them all.<?php break;}
case 78:{?>And David and Solomon, when they gave judgment concerning the field, when people ' s sheep had strayed and browsed therein by night; and We were witnesses to their judgment.<?php break;}
case 79:{?>And We made Solomon to understand ( the case ); and unto each of them We gave judgment and knowledge. And We subdued the hills and the birds to hymn ( His ) praise along with David. We were the doers ( thereof ).<?php break;}
case 80:{?>And We taught him the art of making garments ( of mail ) to protect you in your daring. Are ye then thankful?<?php break;}
case 81:{?>And unto Solomon ( We subdued ) the wind in its raging. It set by His command toward the land which We had blessed. And of everything We are aware.<?php break;}
case 82:{?>And of the evil ones ( subdued We unto him ) some who dived ( for pearls ) for him and did other work, and We were warders unto them.<?php break;}
case 83:{?>And Job, when he cried unto his Lord, ( saying ) : Lo! adversity afflicteth me, and Thou art Most Merciful of all who show mercy.<?php break;}
case 84:{?>Then We heard his prayer and removed that adversity from which he suffered, and We gave him his household ( that he had lost ) and the like thereof along with them, a mercy from Our store, and a remembrance for the worshippers;<?php break;}
case 85:{?>And ( mention ) Ishmael, and Idris, and Dhul-Kifl. All were of the steadfast.<?php break;}
case 86:{?>And We brought them in unto Our mercy. Lo! they are among the righteous.<?php break;}
case 87:{?>And ( mention ) Dhun Nun, when he went off in anger and deemed that We had no power over him, but he cried out in the darkness, saying : There is no God save Thee. Be Thou glorified! I have been a wrong doer.<?php break;}
case 88:{?>Then We heard his prayer and saved him from the anguish. Thus We save believers.<?php break;}
case 89:{?>And Zachariah, when he cried unto his Lord : My Lord! Leave me not childless, though Thou art the best of inheritors.<?php break;}
case 90:{?>Then We heard his prayer, and bestowed upon him John, and adjusted his wife ( to bear a child ) for him. Lo! they used to vie one with the other in good deeds, and they cried unto Us in longing and in fear, and were submissive unto Us.<?php break;}
case 91:{?>And she who was chaste, therefor We breathed into her ( something ) of Our spirit and made her and her son a token for ( all ) peoples.<?php break;}
case 92:{?>Lo! this, your religion, is one religion, and I am your Lord, so worship Me.<?php break;}
case 93:{?>And they have broken their religion ( into fragments ) among them, ( yet ) all are returning unto Us.<?php break;}
case 94:{?>Then whoso doeth good works and is a believer, there will be no rejection of his effort Lo! We record ( it ) for him.<?php break;}
case 95:{?>And there is a ban upon any community which We have destroyed : that they shall not return,<?php break;}
case 96:{?>Until, when Gog and Magog are let loose, and they hasten out of every mound.<?php break;}
case 97:{?>And the True Promise draweth nigh; then behold them, starring wide ( in terror ), the eyes of those who disbelieve! ( They say ) : Alas for us! We ( lived ) in forgetfulness of this. Ah, but we were wrong doers!<?php break;}
case 98:{?>Lo! ye ( idolaters ) and that which ye worship beside Allah are fuel of hell. Thereunto ye will come.<?php break;}
case 99:{?>If these had been Gods they would not have come thither, but all wilt abide therein.<?php break;}
case 100:{?>Therein wailing is their portion, and therein they hear not.<?php break;}
case 101:{?>Lo! those unto whom kindness hath gone forth before from Us, they wilt be far removed from thence.<?php break;}
case 102:{?>They will not hear the slightest sound thereof, while they abide in that which their souls desire.<?php break;}
case 103:{?>The Supreme Horror will not grieve them, and the angels will welcome them, ( saying ) : This is your Day which ye were promised;<?php break;}
case 104:{?>The Day when We shall roll up the heavens and a recorder rolleth up a written scroll. As We began the first creation, We shall repeat it. ( It is ) a promise ( binding ) upon Us. Lo! We are to perform it.<?php break;}
case 105:{?>And verity We have written in the Scripture, after the Reminder : My righteous slaves will inherit the earth :<?php break;}
case 106:{?>Lo! there is a plain statement for folk who are devout.<?php break;}
case 107:{?>We sent thee not save as a mercy for the peoples.<?php break;}
case 108:{?>Say : It is only inspired in me that your God is One God. Will ye then surrender ( unto Him )!<?php break;}
case 109:{?>But if they are averse, then say : I have warned you all alike, although I know not whether nigh or far is that which ye are promised.<?php break;}
case 110:{?>Lo! He knoweth that which is said openly, and that which ye conceal.<?php break;}
case 111:{?>And I know not but that this may be a trial for you, and enjoyment for a while.<?php break;}
case 112:{?>He saith : My Lord! Judge Thou with truth. Our Lord is the Beneficent, whose help is to be implored against that which ye ascribe ( unto Him ).<?php break;}
}?>